Start from the main branch

git checkout main
git pull origin main


Create a hotfix branch

git checkout -b hotfix/issue-name


Example:

git checkout -b hotfix/login-bug


Make your changes and commit

git add .
git commit -m "Fix: resolved login token validation bug"


Push the branch to GitHub

git push origin hotfix/login-bug


Open a Pull Request (PR)

Go to your GitHub repository ‚Üí ‚ÄúPull requests‚Äù tab ‚Üí ‚ÄúNew pull request‚Äù.

Compare hotfix/login-bug ‚Üí main.

Add reviewers and a clear description (what issue it fixes).

After review, merge and delete the branch

git checkout main
git pull origin main
git merge hotfix/login-bug
git push origin main
git branch -d hotfix/login-bug

üß† Best Practices

Prefix hotfix branches with hotfix/

Keep them small and focused on one urgent issue

Merge directly into main (and back into develop if using Git Flow)

Tag the release after merging (e.g., v2.3.1)
